<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,658]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,298,391,417]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kuwayama, S." box="[305,523,392,418]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref13212" refString="Kuwayama, S. (1964) On the Neuroptera of the Ryukyus. Insecta Matsumurana, 27, 38 - 48." type="journal article" year="1964">Kuwayama (1964)</bibRefCitation>
firstly recorded this species from Ishigaki Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1176,392,418]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and he identified it as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[151,280,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Corydalidae" genus="Neochauliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[151,280,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">N. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi, F." box="[297,495,432,458]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" pagination="18 - 19" refId="ref13042" refString="Hayashi, F. (1989 b) Neochauliodes sinensis (Walker) and N. azumai Asahina on Ishigaki and Iriomote Islands, Southern Ryukyus. Gekkan - Mushi, 222, 18 - 19. (in Japanese)." type="journal article" year="1989">Hayashi (1989b)</bibRefCitation>
also recorded 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[673,802,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Corydalidae" genus="Neochauliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[673,802,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">N. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Iriomote Island neighboring to Ishigaki Island. However, this species distinctly differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[678,805,472,497]" class="Insecta" family="Corydalidae" genus="Neochauliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[678,805,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">N. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the wing patterns and the male tenth sternum with the apex strongly inflated in lateral view. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[681,809,512,537]" class="Insecta" family="Corydalidae" genus="Neochauliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[681,809,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">N. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the median transverse band on the forewing is long and narrow, and the apex of the male tenth sternum is not inflated. The prothorax in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2005" box="[1127,1229,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Corydalidae" genus="Neochauliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigris">
<emphasis box="[1127,1229,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">N. nigris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Ishigaki and Iriomote Islands is bright yellow, while it is a little dull and marked with a pair of brownish vittae on the lateral margins in that from the Chinese mainland.
</paragraph>
